One year ago Stevie won his 1st European Championship.

Since then after winning more and more major titles his confidence is through the roof, he truly feels unbeatable he no longer gets nervous or atleast 
no longer shows it. 

I believe its the level of confidence hes gained of constantly competing constantly training constantly winning.

Since day one Stevie wanted the fame and the glory non of it was influenced on him he was just born with that desire. 

His love of winning is only superseded by his hate of losing.

Only thing we can do as parents is support him and try to provide him with all the tools he needs in life in order to achieve his dreams. 

@levelxblack athlete

Stevies plan in this 1st match was to pull guard into close guard and work a submission from bottom. 

You can see him use a fake muscle sweep in order to better his position in close guard. His plan was to finish a submission from bottom before the 1 minute mark. He positions himself in order to easily get his leg over and go belly down.

If he was not able to get a submission before the 1 minute he was going to sweep as hes been working on varies attacks from bottom at the academy. The goal is to make sure Stevie becomes more familiar with being on his back and working his bottom game so he can be a well rounded fighter in all aspects of Jiujitsu  @artofjiujitsu

@levelxblack

When you want to get better, you track down the Best. This is the secret that nobody wants you to know. 

It takes humility to reach out to others for help and assistance. It’s takes Faith to do things others only dream of. 

Create a network of people committed to hard work, success, and execution at the highest level, and you’ll be forced to level up. 

Commit your way to the Lord and in all things He will rise you up. 

These kids have made a decision who they want to be, and us parents have sacrificed our lives (literally) to help facilitate their dreams and make it happen‼️

The road to the Tulsa Nationals @rollerwrestling has been one of ups & downs, sadness & joy; however, we wouldn’t have it any other way. Nothing worth having is easy, and success will cost you every time. 

You are the company you Keep! 

Special Shout out to @so_cal_hammers for having us out to camp and opening the door. We appreciate you‼️
